description.narrative: Some 12,274 basic education learners (6,551 girls and 5,723 boys) in schools accessed learning in child-friendly and gender-sensitive environments. Of the 9,461 students accessing extra academic tutorials in 45 public junior high schools in low-performing districts, 5,883 obtained an annual average of 80% or higher in the four core curriculum subjects. The capacity of 3,274 teachers (653 female and 2,621 male) to deliver child-centred and gender responsive-teaching and effective classroom management was enhanced. | Status:Met | As-of Date:26/12/2019
